                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 195.1/400a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State, February 13, 1915</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1915-02-13">February 13, 1915</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The Russian Ambassador called about February 1 and, referring to the possibility
                    of purchasing belligerent ships if the ship purchase bill passed, stated that
                    his Government adhered to the French position on the subject. I refused to
                    discuss the question with him on the ground that, as the bill did not compel the
                    purchase of belligerent ships, we might not have to consider the question.</p>
            </div>
